&lt;p&gt;This course requires writing a final paper. Here are a couple of articles that may help.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;"Writing Empirical Papers: 6 Rules &amp;amp; 12 Recommendations", Christopher Adolph, &lt;a href="http://faculty.washington.edu/cadolph/503/papers.pdf"&gt;http://faculty.washington.edu/cadolph/503/papers.pdf&lt;/a&gt;. Written for previous versions of 503 course and still applicable both to this course and beyond.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Gary King, "Publication, Publication", &lt;a href="http://gking.harvard.edu/files/paperspub.pdf"&gt;http://gking.harvard.edu/files/paperspub.pdf&lt;/a&gt;. Advice on how to turn a class project into a publication.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
